Kh1 Bf8 16. Bb5 Qa5 17. Nac3 Rxe3 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Bxd7 Qxa2 {Drasko,M (2465)
-Sokolov,I (2545) Yugoslavia 1988 0-1}) (5. Qc2 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. e3 c5 8. Nf3
Be7 9. Be2 Nbd7 10. O-O O-O 11. dxc5 Ne4 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. cxb6 Nxb6 14. Rac1
g5 15. Nd4 Rac8 16. Qb3 Nd2 17. Qc2 Nxf1 18. Nf5 Qf6 19. Bxf1 Rfd8 {Savitskaya,
E (2170)-Petrov,J (2355) Moscow 1996 1-0 (34)}) 5... h6 6. Bxf6 gxf6 {Black
has the pair of bishops} 7. Qg4 {Black is behind in developement} Nc6 8. Nf3 h5
{Black threatens to win material: h5xg4} 9. Qf4 {White has an active position}
(9. Qh3 Bb4 $11) 9... Bd6 (9... Bh6 10. Qh4 $15) 10. e5 (10. Qe3 $142 $5 $11 {
should not be overlooked}) 10... fxe5 $15 11. dxe5 (11. Nxe5 $142 Qe7 12. Nxc6
Bxf4 13. Nxe7 Kxe7 14. h4 $17) 11... Be7 (11... Nxe5 $142 $5 12. Nxe5 f6 $17)
12. a3 {Black has a cramped position} (12. O-O-O Bf8 13. Ne4 Bh6 $14) 12... Rg8
13. Ne4 $4 {a transit from better to worse} (13. h4 $142 $11 {and White can
hope to live}) 13... Rg4 $17 14. Nf6+ Bxf6 15. Qxf6 {[%tqu "En","","","",
"c6e5","",10]} Nxe5 $1 {Remove defender: e5} 16. Qxd8+ (16. Nxe5 Qxf6 {Remove
defender}) (16. Qxe5 Re4+ {Decoy Double attack}) 16... Rxd8 17. Nxe5 Re4+ 18.
Kd2 Rxe5 19. f3 (19. Rc1 $5 $17) 19... d5 $19 20. cxd5 Rdxd5+ 21. Kc2 Rc5+ 22.
Kb3 $4 {shortens the misery for White} (22. Kd2 $19) 22... Bd5+ 23. Ka4 (23.
Bc4 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game} Rxc4 24. Rad1 Re2 $19)
23... Bc6+ (23... Ra5+ 24. Kb4 Re3 25. Bb5+ Ke7 26. Bd3 Rxd3 27. Rac1 Rb3#) 24.
Kb3 $19 Re3+ 25. Ka2 Bd5+ 26. Kb1 (26. Bc4 {otherwise it's curtains at once}
Rxc4 27. Rad1 Rc2+ 28. Ka1 Rxg2 29. h4 $19) 26... Re1# 0-1

