8. d3 Nc7 9. Be3 Ne6 10. Qd2 Re8 11. Nh4 Ned4 12. f4 e6 13. Nf3 d6 14. Bf2 f5
15. Rae1 Bd7 16. Nxd4 cxd4 17. Nb5 Qb8 18. exf5 gxf5 19. Bxc6 bxc6 {Ozhegov,V 
(2202)-Kazancev,V (2323) Togliatti 2007 1/2-1/2 (55)}) (5. d3 d6 6. Be2 h6 7.
h3 e5 8. g4 Nge7 9. Rg1 Rb8 10. Bd2 a6 11. h4 Nd4 12. g5 h5 13. Nxd4 cxd4 14.
Nd5 Nxd5 15. cxd5 Bd7 16. Qb3 O-O 17. Qa3 Re8 18. O-O-O Qb6 19. Kb1 Bf8 {
Teodorescu,I (2265)-Seder,N (2189) Olanesti 2013 1/2-1/2 (45)}) 5... d6 {
Prevents intrusion on e5} 6. O-O Nf6 7. d3 O-O 8. Bg5 a6 {Controls b5} 9. Qd2
Rb8 10. Rad1 b5 11. b3 Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Bxf3 {White has the pair of bishops}
Nd4 {The black knight is well posted.} 14. Bg4 Nxg4 15. hxg4 b4 {Black
threatens to win material: b4xc3} 16. Nd5 {White threatens to win material:
Nd5xe7} Ne6 $4 {a weak move, ruining a winning position} (16... Nc6 17. Bh4 $11
) 17. Bh6 (17. Nxe7+ $142 {and White wins} Kh8 18. Nxg6+ fxg6 19. Bxd8 Nxd8 20.
Qg5 $18) 17... Bc3 (17... Nd4 $142 $5 $11 {would keep Black in the game}) 18.
Nxc3 $16 bxc3 19. Qxc3 Nd4 20. Rde1 Re8 21. f4 e5 22. g5 (22. Qc1 a5 $16) 22...
Ne6 (22... a5 $5 $14 {is worth looking at}) 23. fxe5 $16 Nd4 24. exd6 Qxd6 25.
Rf6 Qe5 26. Qd2 Qc7 (26... Ne6 27. Qe3 $16) 27. Ref1 $18 Re7 28. Qf2 (28. Rxa6
Qg3 $18) 28... Rd8 (28... Ne6 $142 $5 $16) 29. Rxa6 $18 Ne6 $4 {leading to a
quick end} (29... Re6 30. Rxe6 Nxe6 $18) 30. Qf6 Rxd3 (30... Ree8 {there is
nothing better in the position} {[%tqu "En","","","","b3b4","",10]} 31. b4 $1 {
final destruction} Qb7 $18) {[%tqu "En","","","","a6e6","",10]} 31. Rxe6 $1 {
