16. a3 Nc7 17. b4 {Schmitzer,K (2305)-Kuban,G (2260) Hessen 1990 1/2-1/2 (67)})
(2... f5 3. exf5 exf5 4. Bd3 g6 5. Nf3 Qe7+ 6. Kf1 Nf6 7. Nc3 Bg7 8. Bg5 c6 9.
Qd2 O-O 10. Re1 Qd8 11. h4 d6 12. h5 Re8 13. hxg6 hxg6 14. Ne2 Nbd7 15. Nh4 Nf8
16. g4 N8h7 17. Nxg6 {Sveshnikov,E (2515)-Trajkovic,D (2230) Pula 1990 1-0}) (
2... d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nc3 $11) 3. c3 $14 {White threatens to win material:
c3xb4} Be7 4. Nf3 {Black's piece can't move: c8} Nf6 {Black threatens to win
material: Nf6xe4} 5. Bd3 O-O 6. O-O Nc6 {Black's piece can't move: c8} 7. Nbd2
b6 8. b4 Bb7 9. Bb2 d5 10. e5 {White gains space} Ne4 (10... Nh5 $5 $14 {
is worthy of consideration}) 11. Nxe4 $16 dxe4 12. Bxe4 Ba6 $4 {but even a
better move would not have saved the game} (12... Qc8 $142 $16) 13. Bxc6 $18
Bxf1 14. Bxa8 (14. Qxf1 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} Qc8 $18) 14... Bxg2 15.
Bc6 Bh3 16. Qd3 Bh4 (16... Qc8 {does not solve anything} 17. Nd2 Bf5 18. Ne4
$18) 17. Qe4 (17. a4 {might be the shorter path} Bf5 18. Qe2 Bg4 $18) 17... Bg5
18. Bc1 Bf5 19. Bxg5 (19. Qe1 $142 {and White takes home the point} Bxc1 20.
Qxc1 $18) 19... Bxe4 $16 20. Bxd8 (20. Bxe4 $5 Qd7 21. a4 $16) 20... Bxc6 $11
21. Bxc7 Bxf3 22. Bd6 {White threatens to win material: Bd6xf8} Rc8 {Black
threatens to win material: Rc8xc3} 23. Rc1 b5 24. Bc5 a6 25. c4 bxc4 26. Rxc4 {
White has a new backward pawn: d4.} Bd5 {A comfortable square for the black
bishop} 27. Rc2 f6 28. exf6 gxf6 29. a3 Kf7 30. Rc3 Re8 31. Bd6 (31. f3 h5 $14)
31... e5 (31... Rd8 $5 32. Rc7+ Kg6 $11) 32. dxe5 $16 fxe5 33. Rc7+ (33. Kf1
Kf6 $16) 33... Ke6 $14 {Black threatens to win material: Ke6xd6} 34. Bc5 {
A classical outpost} Rg8+ 35. Kf1 Bc4+ 36. Ke1 Rg1+ 37. Kd2 Rg8 (37... Ra1 $5
$16) 38. Rxh7 Rd8+ 39. Ke3 Rd3+ 40. Ke4 Rxa3 41. Re7+ Kf6 42. Rxe5 Bd3+ (42...
Rh3 $5 $16) 43. Kf4 $18 Ra2 44. Bd4 Bg6 $4 {terrible, but the game is lost in
any case} (44... Kf7 $142 $18) 45. Re2+ (45. Re2+ Kf7 46. Rxa2 Bd3 47. Ke5 Ke7
48. f4 Kf7 49. f5 Ke8 50. Ra5 Bc4 51. f6 Kf8 52. Rc5 Bb3 53. h4 Ke8 54. h5 Ba2
55. Rc7 Bb3 56. h6 Kd8 57. Kd6 Bf7 58. Rxf7 Ke8 59. Rd7 Kf8 60. h7 a5 61. h8=Q#
) 1-0

