8. Ngf3 c4 9. Qxb6 axb6 10. a3 b5 11. O-O Be7 12. Ne5 $146 (12. h3 O-O 13. g4
Bg6 14. Nh4 Nd7 15. Nxg6 hxg6 16. Bf3 f5 17. g5 Kf7 18. Kg2 Rh8 19. Kg3 Nb6 20.
Rac1 Ke8 21. h4 Kd7 22. Rh1 Nd8 23. Be5 Rh7 24. h5 Nf7 25. hxg6 Rxh1 26. Rxh1
Nxe5 {Jadrijevic,A (2242)-Brumen,D (2383) Zagreb 2008 1-0 (66)}) 12... O-O 13.
h3 {Covers g4} Nxe5 14. Bxe5 Nd7 15. Bg3 Ra6 (15... Nb6 16. Ra2 $15) 16. Nf3 h6
{Prevents intrusion on g5} 17. Ne5 {White threatens to win material: Ne5xd7}
Nb6 18. Bg4 Bh7 19. f4 $2 (19. Rad1 $142 $5 $15 {is a viable option}) 19... Na4
$17 20. Rf2 Bf5 (20... f6 $142 $5 21. Nd7 Rd8 $17) 21. Bh5 Nb6 22. Re1 g6 {
Black threatens to win material: g6xh5} 23. Bf3 Bf6 (23... Be4 24. Rd2 $15) 24.
e4 $11 dxe4 25. Bxe4 Bxe4 26. Rxe4 Rd8 (26... Be7 27. Rf1 $11) 27. Ng4 Bg7 28.
Bh4 {White threatens to win material: Bh4xd8} Rd5 29. Bf6 Nd7 30. Bxg7 Kxg7 31.
Ne5 Nf6 {Black threatens to win material: Nf6xe4} 32. Re1 h5 33. g3 Rd8 34. Kg2
Nd5 {The knight is not easily driven from d5} 35. Kf3 $4 {releasing the
pressure on the opponent} (35. Nf3 $142 $14 {and White is still in the game})
35... f6 $17 36. Nxg6 (36. Rfe2 $17) 36... Kxg6 $19 37. Rfe2 Kf7 38. Kf2 $6 {
instead of fighting back} (38. g4 hxg4+ 39. hxg4 Rh8 $19) 38... f5 (38... h4 {
and Black can already relax} 39. Kf3 hxg3 40. h4 $19) 39. Re5 (39. Kf3 Rg8 $19)
39... Rb6 (39... h4 $142 {makes it even easier for Black} 40. R5e2 $19) 40. Kf3
Rc8 (40... Rg8 41. Rc1 $19) 41. Rg1 Nf6 42. Rge1 Ne4 (42... Rh8 43. Rf1 $19)
43. Rg1 (43. g4 Kf6 44. gxf5 exf5 $19) 43... Rg8 (43... Rh8 44. Ke2 $19) 44.
Rg2 Rd8 (44... Nf6 45. Rg1 $19) 45. Re2 (45. g4 hxg4+ 46. hxg4 Nd6 $17) 45...
Rd5 46. Rg2 (46. Rh2 $142 $19) 46... Rxe5 47. fxe5 Ng5+ 48. Ke3 Ra6 49. h4 (49.
Rh2 $19) 49... Ne4 50. Kf3 (50. Kf4 $19 {is still a small chance}) 50... Ra8
51. Ke3 Rg8 52. Kf4 (52. Ke2 {doesn't do any good} Ke7 $19) 52... Rg4+ 53. Kf3
Ke7 54. Rg1 Kd7 55. Rg2 Kc6 56. Re2 (56. Rg1 {the only chance to get some
counterplay} Kd5 57. Rg2 $19) 56... Rxg3+ 57. Kf4 Rg4+ 58. Kf3 Rxh4 59. Rg2 Rg4
60. Re2 h4 61. Rxe4 Rxe4 62. Kg2 (62. a4 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} Rg4
63. b3 cxb3 64. axb5+ Kxb5 65. Ke2 b2 66. c4+ Kxc4 67. Kf3 b1=Q 68. Kf2 Qg1+
69. Ke2 Kxd4 70. Kf3 Qg2#) 62... Re3 63. Kf2 (63. Kg1 {doesn't change anything
anymore} Rg3+ 64. Kf2 f4 65. d5+ Kxd5 66. Ke2 h3 67. Kf2 h2 68. b3 h1=Q 69.
bxc4+ Ke4 70. cxb5 Rg2#) 63... f4 (63... Rg3 64. a4 f4 65. axb5+ Kd5 66. b6 h3
67. b4 h2 68. Ke2 h1=Q 69. Kf2 Rh3 70. Ke2 Rh2#) 64. Kg2 (64. b3 {doesn't get
the cat off the tree} cxb3 65. a4 bxa4 66. Kg2 b2 67. d5+ Kc5 68. dxe6 Rxc3 69.
e7 b1=Q 70. Kf2 Qb2+ 71. Kf1 Rc1#) 64... h3+ (64... Rg3+ 65. Kf1 h3 66. Kf2 Kd5
67. b3 h2 68. bxc4+ Ke4 69. cxb5 h1=Q 70. a4 Rg2#) 65. Kf2 (65. Kg1 {is not
the saving move} Re2 66. Kh1 f3 67. a4 bxa4 68. d5+ Kxd5 69. Kg1 Rg2+ 70. Kh1
f2 71. b4 f1=Q#) 65... Rg3 (65... Rg3 66. Kf1 h2 67. d5+ exd5 68. b4 h1=Q+ 69.
Kf2 Rg2+ 70. Kf3 Qf1#) 0-1

