position} Nbd7 {Black has a cramped position. Black's piece can't move: c8} 8.
Bh6 e5 9. Bxg7 Kxg7 10. O-O-O (10. a4 $142 $11) 10... d5 (10... b5 $142 $5 {
must definitely be considered} 11. dxe5 dxe5 $11) 11. dxe5 (11. exd5 e4 12. Ne5
cxd5 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. Bxd5 Nf6 $16) 11... dxc4 $14 12. exf6+ Qxf6 13. h4 h5
14. Ng5 Ne5 (14... Qe7 $5 $14 {should be examined more closely}) 15. f4 $16 Ng4
16. e5 Qe7 17. Nce4 Bf5 18. Nd6 a5 (18... Be6 19. Nxe6+ fxe6 20. g3 $16) 19.
Nxc4 (19. Nxf5+ gxf5 20. Qd7 Qxd7 21. Rxd7 Kg8 $18) 19... Qc5 (19... Be6 20.
Nb6 Rad8 21. Qxa5 $16) 20. Qd4 (20. Nd6 $142 Nh6 21. Nxb7 $18) 20... Qb4 $4 {
an oversight. But Black was lost anyway.} (20... Qxd4 21. Rxd4 Rae8 22. Nd6 $16
) 21. Nd6 (21. e6+ $142 {finishes off the opponent} Nf6 22. a3 $18) 21... c5
22. Nxf5+ gxf5 23. Qxb4 (23. Qd2 $5 Rfd8 24. Qxb4 cxb4 25. Rxd8 Rxd8 26. e6 $18
