Nc5 13. h3 Ne6 14. Ne2 Ng5 15. Nc1 Bb4 16. c3 Bf8 17. Qe2 Bxh3 18. gxh3 Nxh3+
19. Kh2 Nf4 20. Qe3 {Jovanovic,S (2290)-Drozdov,I (2375) Arandjelovac 1993 0-1}
) (5... c6 6. d4 Nbd7 7. Be2 O-O 8. O-O Re8 9. Qd2 Qc7 10. Rad1 Nf8 11. Rfe1
Ng6 12. h3 Bd7 13. Bf1 Rad8 14. Qc1 Bc8 15. dxe5 dxe5 16. Rxd8 Rxd8 17. Rd1
Rxd1 18. Qxd1 b5 19. Nd2 Bc5 20. g3 {Strenzwilk,D (2227)-Shocron,R (2260)
Parsipanny 2002 1/2-1/2 (59)}) 6. Be2 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7 8. d4 Bxf3 9. Bxf3 exd4
10. Qxd4 {White has the pair of bishops} Ne5 11. Qd1 c6 {Secures b5+d5} 12. Na4
(12. Be2 Ned7 $14) 12... Qc7 13. Re1 Rad8 14. c4 Rfe8 15. Bxe5 (15. h3 a6 $11)
15... dxe5 $15 {Opposite coloured bishops appeared.} 16. Qc2 Rd7 17. Rad1 Red8
18. Rxd7 Rxd7 19. Rd1 Rd4 20. Rxd4 exd4 {Black has a new passed pawn: d4} 21.
Qd3 c5 (21... Qe5 22. g3 $15) 22. h3 {Covers g4} h6 23. b4 (23. Nb2 Nd7 $11)
23... b6 24. b5 {This push gains space} (24. bxc5 Bxc5 25. Nb2 g6 $15) 24...
Nd7 (24... Qf4 25. g3 Qc1+ 26. Kg2 $17) 25. Nb2 Ne5 {Black threatens to win
material: Ne5xd3} 26. Qd1 Qd6 27. Nd3 $2 {The white knight is safe in front of
d4} (27. Be2 $142 $5 $15 {would allow White to play on}) 27... Nxc4 $19 28. Qb3
$2 (28. g3 Qc7 $17) 28... Ne5 $4 {letting the wind out of his own sails} (28...
Nd2 {seems even better} 29. Qc2 Nxf3+ 30. gxf3 Qg6+ 31. Kh2 $19) 29. Bh5 $2 (
29. Nxe5 $142 Qxe5 30. g3 $17) 29... g6 $4 {lets it slip away} (29... c4 $142 {
secures the win} 30. Bxf7+ Kxf7 31. Nxe5+ Qxe5 32. Qxc4+ Kf6 $19) 30. Nxe5 $11
{White has a mate threat} Qxe5 {Black forks: e4+h5} 31. Bxg6 {White has a mate
threat} Qf6 32. Bh5 Qe6 {Black threatens to win material: Qe6xe4} 33. Qg3+ Kh7
34. Qf3 {White threatens to win material: Qf3xf7} Bf6 35. Qf5+ $4 {gives the
opponent new chances} (35. e5 $142 {would keep White in the game} Qxe5 36. Bxf7
$11) 35... Qxf5 $19 36. exf5 Kg7 (36... c4 37. Bf3 d3 $19) 37. Kf1 $2 (37. Be2
$142 $11 {would allow White to play on}) 37... d3 $17 38. Bd1 $4 {the pressure
is too much, White crumbles} (38. Ke1 $142 Bc3+ 39. Kd1 $19) 38... c4 $19 39.
f4 (39. Ba4 $19 {is the last straw}) 39... c3 40. Ke1 (40. Be2 {does not win a
prize} c2 41. Bxd3 c1=Q+ 42. Ke2 Bd4 43. f6+ Kxf6 44. Bh7 Qe3+ 45. Kd1 Bc3 46.
Kc2 Qd2+ 47. Kb3 Bb2 48. a4 Qc3+ 49. Ka2 Ba3 50. g4 Qb2#) 40... Bh4+ 41. Kf1 c2
42. Bxc2 dxc2 43. f6+ (43. Ke2 {cannot change what is in store for White} c1=Q
44. a4 Qc2+ 45. Ke3 Bf2+ 46. Kf3 Bc5 47. Kg3 Qf2+ 48. Kh2 Be3 49. f6+ Kxf6 50.
f5 Bf4+ 51. Kh1 Qf1#) 43... Kxf6 44. g3 (44. Ke2 {is not much help} c1=Q 45.
Kd3 Kf5 46. g3 Bxg3 47. a4 Be1 48. h4 Qc3+ 49. Ke2 Qd2+ 50. Kf1 Qf2#) 44...
Bxg3 (44... Bxg3 45. Kg2 Be1 46. Kh2 c1=Q 47. Kh1 Qc2 48. a4 Bg3 49. Kg1 Qh2+
50. Kf1 Qf2#) (44... c1=Q+ 45. Kg2 Qe3 46. gxh4 Kf5 47. a4 Kxf4 48. h5 Qe2+ 49.
Kg1 Kg3 50. h4 Qe1#) 0-1

